# Normalise line endings in the repository.
#
# Without this, macOS and Windows CI flip every file back and forth: the first
# commit of the starter pack produced an LF-to-CRLF warning on all 24 files.
# Both platforms are release targets (ARCHITECTURE.md 12), so this is not
# cosmetic - it is what stops the two from fighting over every diff.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must keep LF even when checked out on Windows: CRLF makes them
# unrunnable in CI containers and in Git Bash.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Windows batch files are the mirror image: they need CRLF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Patch payloads retain upstream context indentation so they remain applicable.
*.patch text eol=lf -whitespace

# Binary assets git must not touch.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.mkv binary
*.mka binary
*.mp4 binary
*.vrm binary
*.inp binary
